title: Construction over, speed limits back up on SR 16
text:
Starting this week, drivers in Tacoma will be able to get to where they are going faster.
Speed limits in some spots along State Route 16 are going back up to 60 mph.
Depending on where you are on a stretch of SR 16, you'll be able to go 5 to 10 mph faster.
The Washington State Department of Transportation had to lower the speed limits along the stretch because of several active construction projects.
During construction, WSDOT said many drivers complained about the lower limits.
In August, crews finished building a ramp thatâ€™s part of a larger project to build HOV lanes on the stretch.
Here are the new limits starting this week:
Westbound State Route 16 from I-5 to Union Avenue is up from 50 to 60 mph. Eastbound State Route 16 from Union Ave to I-5 is up from 40 to 60 mph. Eastbound State Route 16 from the Pearl Street Exit to Union Avenue is up from 55 to 60 mph.
The new speed limits are in effect now and WSDOT says new speed limit signs are being put up this week.
